    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically robust 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2), featuring the 3.6L flat-six engine equipped with VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing and lift. Power is delivered through a G96 6-speed manual transaxle, offering precise shift gates and mechanical engagement. This specimen has been proactively maintained with an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a recent rear main seal (RMS) replacement. The chassis retains its factory poise, utilizing a sophisticated multi-link rear suspension and MacPherson struts that provide exceptional lateral stiffness and communicative feedback. Braking is handled by four-piston monobloc calipers over vented, cross-drilled rotors, ensuring consistent thermal management under load. This is a driver-focused example with a linear power band and excellent oil pressure, showing only honest cosmetic wear consistent with its enthusiast pedigree.",
